# Inspectio: no v1 code dependency

When editing **`src/inspectio/`**, repo-root **`tests/`**, or **`pyproject.toml`** for the greenfield stack:

- **Do not** `import inspectio_exercise` or import from **`v1_obsolete/project/src`** (or copy those modules in).
- **Do not** port behavior by mirroring **`v1_obsolete/**`** tests as the source of truth; for the **v2** line follow **`v2_obsolete/plans/NEW_SYSTEM_IMPLEMENTATION_BLUEPRINT.md`**, **`plans/openapi.yaml`**, **`v2_obsolete/plans/IMPLEMENTATION_PHASES.md`**, and **§28** **TC-** ids. **V3** design may replace these; default to **`plans/openapi.yaml`** plus any new v3 spec when present.
- **`v1_obsolete/plans/*`** is for **explicit blueprint traps** (e.g. §2.3) only — not a parallel spec.

Normative detail: archived blueprint **§29.11** and **`v2_obsolete/plans/IMPLEMENTATION_PHASES.md`** section **`v1_obsolete` boundary**.

Docker **mock-sms** is **`deploy/mock-sms/Dockerfile`** (see **`docker-compose.yml`**); **do not** build it from **`v1_obsolete/`**. Do not route API/worker/notification through v1 **`inspectio_exercise`** at runtime.
